a Christian

05:09.143 --> 05:10.294
because of a song
I heard

05:10.378 --> 05:12.730
or a book I read,
as much as I like to read.

05:12.813 --> 05:16.066
Uh, I came to experience
the realness of Christ

05:16.150 --> 05:18.569
through the people
in his church.

05:18.652 --> 05:20.638
<i>I'm a Christian, not because</i>

05:20.721 --> 05:23.907
somebody explained the nuts and
bolts of Christianity to me but

05:23.991 --> 05:26.702
because people were willing
to be the nuts and bolts.

05:34.918 --> 05:36.712
Come on,
let's go!

05:49.933 --> 05:51.643
<i>I guess you could say
my story began</i>

05:51.727 --> 05:53.562
<i>in a small town
in Indiana.</i>

05:57.524 --> 05:59.777
<i>My dad was a farmer</i>

05:59.860 --> 06:03.447
<i>and easily, easily the hardest
working man that I know.</i>

06:03.530 --> 06:04.857
<i>Like most boys,
I grew up</i>

06:04.941 --> 06:08.619
<i>wanting to be exactly like him,
exactly like my dad.</i>

06:08.702 --> 06:11.789
<i>But I discovered
at a pretty early age,</i>

06:11.872 --> 06:14.041
<i>time and time again that</i>

06:14.124 --> 06:16.085
<i>I wasn't really cut
out to be a farmer.</i>

06:28.389 --> 06:29.723
Hold the light.

06:29.765 --> 06:31.266
What's wrong
with it, Dad?

06:31.350 --> 06:33.060
<i>Damn light, son!</i>

06:40.692 --> 06:43.737
It's the pistons.

06:43.779 --> 06:45.155
What did you
fill it with?

06:45.239 --> 06:47.825
Gasoline.
Like you said.

06:47.908 --> 06:49.576
Like I said?

06:49.660 --> 06:51.286
<i>Not like I said,
'cause I didn't say</i>

06:51.370 --> 06:53.956
<i>I didn't say
nothing about gasoline.</i>

06:54.039 --> 06:57.334
<i>Of all
the damn fool things.</i>

06:57.418 --> 06:58.585
Lean over here, boy.
Come here.

06:58.627 --> 07:01.797
<i>What's that say?</i>

07:01.880 --> 07:03.340
Speak up, Wayne!
What's it say?

07:03.424 --> 07:04.591
"Diesel."

07:04.675 --> 07:09.012
That's right.
Diesel.

07:09.096 --> 07:12.850
Because you can't put
gasoline in the tractor, son.

07:12.933 --> 07:13.934
I'm sorry, Dad.

07:15.602 --> 07:17.354
Well, sorry isn't going
to fix this, boy.

07:17.438 --> 07:18.772
Damn!

07:35.789 --> 07:39.126
<i>My mom and dad
raised five of us kids</i>

07:39.168 --> 07:43.797
<i>and, you know, most of the time
money was pretty scarce.</i>

07:43.839 --> 07:46.216
<i>And when I was little, my
baby brother passed a way.</i>

07:46.300 --> 07:49.470
<i>And that was
often hard for them.</i>

07:49.511 --> 07:51.763
<i>Even as a boy,
I wanted to help.</i>

07:56.059 --> 07:59.730
<i>But I couldn't.</i>

07:59.813 --> 08:01.857
<i>Why didn't you tell me
you got the tractor</i>

08:01.940 --> 08:05.235
<i>stuck in the field
this morning?</i>

08:05.319 --> 08:06.528
<i>Speak up, Do)'-</i>

08:06.612 --> 08:08.697
I thought
you'd be mad.

08:08.780 --> 08:12.993
I just don't understand why
everything you touch ends up busted.

08:42.856 --> 08:45.234
<i>I wish you'd be
more gentle with him.</i>

08:45.317 --> 08:49.363
<i>More gentle?</i>

08:49.446 --> 08:51.281
That's the last
thing to be.

08:51.365 --> 08:53.534
<i>He needs to toughen up,
that's what.</i>

08:53.617 --> 08:55.702
<i>He's got his damn
head in the clouds.</i>

08:55.744 --> 08:57.871
He needs to know
you love him.

08:57.955 --> 09:00.207
That boy needs to stay
away from the tractor.

09:00.249 --> 09:03.043
<i>Last week,
it was the engine.</i>

09:03.126 --> 09:04.545
<i>Today he got not one,</i>

09:04.628 --> 09:06.964
but four wheels
stuck in holes.

09:07.047 --> 09:09.716
- John, he's just trying...
- Four, Neva.

09:09.758 --> 09:13.387
Four.  The repairs
cost 300 dollars,

09:13.470 --> 09:15.639
not to mention the
lost time on the farm.

09:15.722 --> 09:18.308
Ain't going to be worried about love

09:18.392 --> 09:20.269
if he is going
hungry, will he?

09:29.820 --> 09:32.656
He's our oldest boy, Neva.

09:32.739 --> 09:34.275
If he doesn't learn,

09:34.358 --> 09:38.328
then how is he going to
take over the farm one day?

09:38.412 --> 09:43.166
Maybe he's not
meant for the farm.

09:45.252 --> 09:46.878
You're a good father.

09:49.923 --> 09:51.258
Hm.

09:59.808 --> 10:01.018
She got it.

10:03.103 --> 10:04.605
She did,
didn't she?

10:11.278 --> 10:14.281
<i>Dad, that's it.</i>

10:14.323 --> 10:16.533
<i>What are you
doing, boy?</i>

10:16.617 --> 10:18.285
John!

10:20.162 --> 10:21.872
Didn't you
like it, Mom?

10:21.955 --> 10:24.750
Yes. Yes,
it's wonderful.

10:29.046 --> 10:30.047
John...

10:37.929 --> 10:39.723
<i>As I got older,
music seemed to be</i>

10:39.806 --> 10:41.391
<i>the only thing
that made sense to me.</i>

10:41.475 --> 10:43.393
<i>I was pretty good at it</i>

10:43.477 --> 10:46.229
<i>and there was something
about sitting at a piano</i>

10:46.313 --> 10:50.317
<i>that just made me feel
like I was home.</i>

10:57.157 --> 10:59.493
<i>How do you think
that God views you?</i>

10:59.576 --> 11:02.162
Have you asked
yourself this?

11:02.204 --> 11:03.747
You should,

11:03.830 --> 11:05.874
<i>because your perception
of God</i>

11:05.957 --> 11:10.087
<i>will have an effect on
every aspect of your life.</i>

11:10.170 --> 11:12.005
<i>In the Book of Romans,</i>

11:12.047 --> 11:15.842
<i>Paul quoting Isaiah
speaks to the truth that</i>

11:15.926 --> 11:19.680
no one is righteous,
how we are all sinners.

11:19.763 --> 11:22.724
<i>But God commanded
his love toward us.</i>

11:24.935 --> 11:28.230
- That was wonderful, Richard.
- Thank you, Mrs. Kellner.

11:28.313 --> 11:31.108
Now why don't you play
it how it was written?

11:32.359 --> 11:33.527
<i>Time to go, son.</i>

11:33.610 --> 11:35.612
He is
my best student.

11:35.696 --> 11:37.698
<i>Well, at least there's
one thing he's good at.</i>

11:37.781 --> 11:38.949
<i>It sure isn't farming.</i>

11:39.032 --> 11:40.492
<i>Let's get, boy.</i>

11:45.205 --> 11:46.873
<i>Growing up, people
would always tell me</i>

11:46.915 --> 11:48.667
<i>that God
loved me</i>

11:48.750 --> 11:50.293
<i>but I had a hard time believing that.</i>

11:50.377 --> 11:54.089
<i>I wondered
if God even liked me.</i>

11:54.172 --> 11:58.927
<i>Maybe it's because people also
told me that my dad loved me.</i>

11:59.010 --> 12:02.264
<i>I mean, my dad and I didn't
connect or we couldn't connect.</i>

12:02.347 --> 12:04.133
<i>The things
he knew and understood</i>

12:04.216 --> 12:08.103
<i>weren't things I knew and
understood and vice versa.</i>

12:08.186 --> 12:12.149
<i>They say that time
heals all wounds</i>

12:12.232 --> 12:14.276
<i>but honestly in our case
it just made things worse.</i>

12:21.908 --> 12:23.326
I hate
being different.

12:25.746 --> 12:27.748
I think God knows
what he's doing, Wayne.

12:27.789 --> 12:30.834
Dad hates it, too.

12:30.917 --> 12:33.420
Your father
loves you.

12:33.503 --> 12:35.505
No, he loves
Dave and Lloyd.

12:35.589 --> 12:37.591
He understands them.

12:37.674 --> 12:41.344
<i>He loves
all of you.</i>

12:41.428 --> 12:43.930
Sometimes I just wish
I was more like them.

12:47.434 --> 12:48.977
I don't belong here.

12:52.981 --> 12:54.649
<i>God's got big plans for you.</i>

12:54.733 --> 12:55.984
<i>I know it.</i>

12:58.111 --> 13:00.781
You are going to do
great things one day.

13:15.796 --> 13:17.464
<i>After high school,</i>

13:17.547 --> 13:19.883
<i>I wasn't sure what
I was going to do.</i>

13:19.966 --> 13:21.843
<i>Home had became a place</i>

13:21.927 --> 13:25.472
<i>where you had to learn
the language of silence.</i>

13:25.514 --> 13:28.809
<i>My dad and I grew apart.</i>

13:28.850 --> 13:34.768
<i>Uh, you know, he grew inward
and I grew bitter.</i>

13:35.899 --> 13:39.569
<i>At that time, my rebellion
was in full swing.</i>

13:39.653 --> 13:42.155
<i>Uh, let's just say
that surrender</i>

13:42.197 --> 13:45.242
<i>doesn't exactly
come naturally to me.</i>

13:45.325 --> 13:47.327
<i>But I quickly learned
that God</i>

13:47.410 --> 13:49.663
<i>can speak to us in some
pretty unexpected ways.</i>

13:53.917 --> 13:57.921
<i>How do you respond to these
accusations from your father?</i>

13:58.004 --> 14:02.884
<i>Do you dare defy the
ordinances of Holy Mother Church ?</i>

14:02.968 --> 14:06.054
<i>How can you stand there
in defiance of your father?</i>

14:06.137 --> 14:08.181
<i>You're bestowed with
riches beyond your worth</i>

14:08.223 --> 14:10.016
<i>and now
you rebuke their value?</i>

14:10.058 --> 14:14.145
<i>By what authority
do you do such things?</i>

14:15.814 --> 14:19.442
<i>I want to live
a life of freedom.</i>

14:19.526 --> 14:21.194
<i>I want to be as free</i>

14:21.236 --> 14:23.905
<i>as the animals
that roam this earth,</i>

14:23.989 --> 14:27.033
<i>as free as the moon
in the night sky.</i>

14:27.117 --> 14:30.745
<i>These earthly possessions,</i>

14:30.829 --> 14:34.249
<i>this noble stature,</i>

14:34.332 --> 14:39.212
<i>the adoration that our
society craves is no use to me.</i>

14:39.296 --> 14:41.256
<i>But you're my son.</i>

14:41.339 --> 14:43.633
<i>I'm no longer
your son.</i>

14:43.717 --> 14:46.261
<i>Saint Francis was wild.
I mean,</i>

14:46.344 --> 14:48.722
<i>he fell madly in
love with Jesus.</i>

14:48.763 --> 14:51.725
<i>As a result of that, he
gave up everything he had.</i>

14:51.808 --> 14:53.894
<i>Why are you doing this?</i>

14:53.977 --> 14:56.897
<i>God calls
to every man.</i>

14:56.938 --> 15:00.609
<i>But not every man responds.</i>

15:00.692 --> 15:02.277
<i>I connected to the story
of Saint Francis</i>

15:02.360 --> 15:04.321
<i>in a lot of ways.</i>

15:04.404 --> 15:07.908
<i>You know, he just had
this radical trust in Christ.</i>

15:07.991 --> 15:10.994
<i>It was a trust
that I didn't have.</i>

15:11.077 --> 15:13.330
<i>But I wanted it.</i>

15:13.413 --> 15:16.750
<i>I knew that deep down if I
wanted to grow that kind of faith,</i>

15:16.791 --> 15:20.587
<i>it wasn't going to happen
by staying at home.</i>

15:20.629 --> 15:21.671
<i>So I left.</i>

15:52.160 --> 15:53.828
<i>You know, it's interesting.</i>

15:53.912 --> 15:55.956
<i>I had reached
a point in my life</i>

15:56.039 --> 15:57.874
<i>where I decided to get
serious about my faith</i>

15:57.958 --> 16:01.252
<i>before I had no faith
to get serious about.</i>

16:01.336 --> 16:03.088
<i>Not that going
to Bible College</i>

16:03.171 --> 16:04.339
<i>is particularly
the place to get serious</i>

16:04.422 --> 16:06.091
<i>about your faith</i>

16:06.174 --> 16:08.218
<i>but nevertheless,
that's where I went.</i>

16:22.315 --> 16:24.818
Hey! What are you
doing with my stuff?

16:24.859 --> 16:26.528
Oh, I thought
this would be okay.

16:26.611 --> 16:28.405
- I prefer to sleep with my...
- You thought...

16:28.488 --> 16:30.740
this would be okay?

16:30.824 --> 16:32.409
Let me ask you
a question.

16:32.492 --> 16:34.035
You ever stare danger
straight in the eye

16:34.119 --> 16:37.330
and live
to tell about it?

16:37.372 --> 16:38.415
Name's Sam.

16:39.666 --> 16:41.209
Just joking, man.

16:41.292 --> 16:42.585
You must be Rich.
Yeah.

16:42.669 --> 16:44.087
Yeah, nice
to meet you, man.

16:44.170 --> 16:45.055
You scared me there
for a second.

16:45.139 --> 16:47.298
I've got kind of a weird
sense of humor.

16:47.382 --> 16:48.842
You should know
that up front.

16:48.883 --> 16:50.677
Hey, I think
that's everything.

16:50.760 --> 16:52.053
<i>Your mom and I are
going to head back.</i>

16:52.137 --> 16:53.221
<i>So...
Cool.</i>

16:53.304 --> 16:54.431
Oh, hi.
I'm Morris.

16:54.514 --> 16:55.724
Hey,Dad.
Hi, Morris.

16:55.807 --> 16:56.975
I'm Rich.
I'm the dad.

16:57.058 --> 16:58.268
It's nice
to meet you.

16:58.351 --> 16:59.936
You can go
now, Dad.

17:00.020 --> 17:01.021
Yeah, we're going
to head back.

17:01.104 --> 17:02.689
Love you, Pops.

17:02.731 --> 17:04.190
<i>I love you, too, man.</i>

17:04.273 --> 17:05.900
You guys have fun.
We'll see you.

17:05.983 --> 17:07.777
- There you go.
- Nice to meet you, Morris.

17:07.861 --> 17:09.779
<i>Hey, um...</i>

17:09.863 --> 17:11.698
I got
a question for you.

17:11.740 --> 17:13.700
<i>You seem kind of like
a handsome guy.</i>

17:13.742 --> 17:15.952
I wasn't really popular
with the girls in high school

17:16.036 --> 17:18.204
so I want you
to shoot me straight.

17:18.288 --> 17:20.915
Does this, uh, beard
make me look fat?

17:23.460 --> 17:25.627
- No, serious.
- I don't know how to answer that question.

17:25.712 --> 17:27.380
<i>That's fair enough.
That's fair enough.</i>

17:29.340 --> 17:30.717
Oh, man.

17:30.759 --> 17:32.218
<i>So you're a bully.</i>

17:44.814 --> 17:49.736
<i>My time at CBC
kind of flew by fast.</i>

17:49.778 --> 17:53.656
<i>Sam and I hit it off well and
became good friends quickly.</i>

17:55.450 --> 17:57.160
<i>Being in
a structured institution,</i>

17:57.243 --> 17:58.953
<i>I found myself asking
a lot of questions</i>

17:59.037 --> 18:01.623
<i>about the church,
about authority.</i>

18:01.706 --> 18:04.000
<i>They weren't always
popular with the faculty.</i>

18:04.084 --> 18:07.128
oh, you play?

18:07.212 --> 18:08.922
Yeah, absolutely.
I play all the time.

18:09.005 --> 18:10.507
- Oh, man.
- Yeah, I saw the case.

18:10.590 --> 18:11.758
- You want to jam?
- Yeah!

18:11.800 --> 18:13.593
<i>Yeah.
For sure.</i>

18:13.635 --> 18:16.638
<i>Sam and I formed
a small band called Zion.</i>

18:16.721 --> 18:19.766
<i>We started off playing at small
coffeeshops around Cincinnati,</i>

18:19.808 --> 18:23.311
<i>and then eventually
in church auditoriums.</i>

18:23.394 --> 18:25.105
<i>The more I played,
the more I realized</i>

18:25.188 --> 18:27.190
<i>that I didn't want
to just play music.</i>

18:27.273 --> 18:30.527
<i>I wanted a ministry.</i>

18:30.610 --> 18:32.654
<i>So we moved off campus
our senior year</i>

18:32.737 --> 18:35.115
<i>with a couple of the other
members of the band.</i>

18:35.156 --> 18:38.159
<i>It was exciting to feel
God working through me</i>

18:38.243 --> 18:42.622
<i>even on a small stage
like Cincinnati.</i>

18:52.048 --> 18:54.968
He is incredible.

18:55.009 --> 18:56.177
He's pretty good.

18:59.806 --> 19:01.766
There he
goes again.

19:07.355 --> 19:09.732
Richard.
Richard.

19:09.816 --> 19:11.109
I thought I told you
you weren't allowed

19:11.192 --> 19:13.069
to play
on campus anymore.

19:13.153 --> 19:15.363
Especially if you're bent
on destroying another piano.

19:15.446 --> 19:17.407
Mr. Walters,
I'm sorry.

19:17.490 --> 19:22.829
I asked Richard to play for
orientation.  It's my fault.

19:22.912 --> 19:24.431
Monday morning,

19:24.514 --> 19:27.208
I want you prepared to quote
the first chapter of Isaiah

19:27.292 --> 19:29.252
in my office
eight a.m. sharp.

19:29.335 --> 19:30.920
I can do that.

19:34.591 --> 19:35.758
Break it up.

19:35.842 --> 19:37.260
It was so good.

19:37.343 --> 19:38.761
Take it easy.
It was just one song.

19:38.845 --> 19:40.146
It was great.
It really was.

19:40.188 --> 19:41.848
I see the Scripture Police got you.

19:41.890 --> 19:43.766
- You noticed that, huh?
- I did.

19:43.850 --> 19:46.686
Thankfully, he's given
me that chapter before.

19:46.769 --> 19:48.563
<i>Man, what's up
with that guy?</i>

19:48.646 --> 19:50.440
It's ridiculous.

19:50.523 --> 19:53.943
Hi. Um, that
was incredible.

19:54.027 --> 19:56.862
I've never heard anything
like that before, ever.

19:57.739 --> 19:59.449
Um, I'm...  hi, I'm Beth.

19:59.532 --> 20:00.909
I'm Rich.

20:00.992 --> 20:02.952
- Nice to meet you.
- You sing?

20:03.036 --> 20:06.539
Uh, yeah.  I mean, just at, like,

20:06.623 --> 20:08.625
church at home.

20:08.708 --> 20:10.084
You should sing
with our band, Zion.

20:10.168 --> 20:11.794
You've never
heard me play.

20:11.878 --> 20:12.988
I mean, sing.

20:13.071 --> 20:15.351
Oh, I'm sure you're fine.
Jesus isn't picky.

20:17.342 --> 20:20.303
Um, this is
my friend, Jess.

20:20.386 --> 20:21.137
Say hi.

20:21.221 --> 20:22.155
<i>Hey!</i>

20:22.239 --> 20:23.232
<i>That was great.</i>

20:23.315 --> 20:25.433
You, too. Or not.
Not you too.

20:25.516 --> 20:27.101
I don't... I don't sing at all.

20:27.185 --> 20:31.481
No, that's not
what I meant. Um...

20:31.564 --> 20:33.900
It was nice
to meet you.

20:33.942 --> 20:36.653
Yeah.

20:36.736 --> 20:38.488
We'll see
you around?

20:38.571 --> 20:40.198
Yep.
Got it.

20:43.910 --> 20:47.080
Ah. She's pretty, huh?

20:47.121 --> 20:49.249
<i>Pretty cute.</i>

20:51.793 --> 20:53.419
<i>I tried my best
to ignore her</i>

20:53.461 --> 20:56.172
<i>and just focus
on Zion or school.</i>

20:56.256 --> 20:58.925
<i>But I couldn't help it.</i>

20:58.967 --> 21:02.762
<i>Uh, from the moment
I met Jess, I...</i>

21:02.804 --> 21:04.597
<i>I couldn't get her
out of my mind.</i>

21:06.683 --> 21:08.601
Sorry about the car.

21:08.643 --> 21:11.187
I pretended to know, like
I know something about cars

21:11.271 --> 21:12.855
for as long as I could
and keep it up.

21:12.939 --> 21:14.224
I think I figured it
out pretty quickly.

21:14.307 --> 21:15.942
- Yeah, sorry about that.
- It's all right.

21:15.984 --> 21:17.694
I'll stick
with the piano.

21:17.777 --> 21:20.029
Hold on.

21:20.113 --> 21:22.115
There are a lot of really
amazing doors on this campus

21:22.156 --> 21:23.491
but these are
probably my favorite.

21:23.574 --> 21:25.451
They're beautiful.

21:25.493 --> 21:27.120
- You want to sit for a bit?
- Sure.

21:28.621 --> 21:30.290
Do you write?

21:30.373 --> 21:32.709
Some.
A journal

21:32.792 --> 21:34.627
Journal?

21:34.669 --> 21:38.006
- How morose of you.
- Hmm.

21:38.089 --> 21:39.674
What do you
write about?

21:39.757 --> 21:43.469
Oh, my dreams.

21:43.511 --> 21:45.680
Fears.

21:45.763 --> 21:50.393
Dreams about what?

21:50.476 --> 21:51.686
<i>About the man I'll marry</i>

21:51.769 --> 21:53.021
and settle down with.

21:55.857 --> 21:58.318
The house we'll live in.

21:58.359 --> 22:00.361
The kids.

22:00.445 --> 22:01.446
The dog.

22:03.781 --> 22:05.158
That's what you
want most.

22:05.199 --> 22:06.776
Yeah.

22:06.860 --> 22:10.747
<i>Yeah, a home and
someone to share it with.</i>

22:10.830 --> 22:13.708
<i>What about your fears?</i>

22:13.791 --> 22:16.961
Being alone.

22:17.045 --> 22:21.007
No, I mean...

22:21.049 --> 22:26.179
I'm terrified
of myself sometimes,

22:26.262 --> 22:30.683
of this loneliness I feel
inside of me.  It's like, um...

22:30.767 --> 22:32.518
it's like a black hole or something.

22:39.859 --> 22:42.862
<i>Even when you're as close as
you can be to another person,</i>

22:42.945 --> 22:47.367
even when you're touching.

22:47.408 --> 22:49.369
That's exactly it.

22:52.038 --> 22:53.206
Feel alone now?

23:18.064 --> 23:21.275
<i>Jess and I were immediately
drawn to each other.</i>

23:21.359 --> 23:22.535
<i>Over the next few months,</i>

23:22.536 --> 23:25.613
<i>I spent some of the most
meaningful days of my life with her</i>

23:25.696 --> 23:29.158
<i>and learning
each other's stories,</i>

23:29.242 --> 23:30.410
<i>and sharing dreams.</i>

23:35.540 --> 23:39.043
<i>We were just two lonely people
who had found each other in the dark.</i>

23:48.970 --> 23:51.764
<i>When I was with Jess,
I felt...</i>

23:51.848 --> 23:55.768
<i>I felt something
I hadn't felt in a long time.</i>

23:55.852 --> 23:57.145
<i>I felt like I was home.</i>

24:04.318 --> 24:10.116
♪    Life goes on    ♪
and so must the song

24:10.158 --> 24:13.286
♪ Doo doo doooo doo ♪

24:24.464 --> 24:26.799
♪ Sing your praise to the Lord ♪

24:26.841 --> 24:29.343
♪   Come on everybody and   ♪
stand up and sing one more

24:29.427 --> 24:32.221
♪ Hallelujah, sing your ♪
praise to the Lord

24:32.305 --> 24:34.891
♪ I can never tell you ♪
- I love it.

24:34.974 --> 24:37.560
Is that the guy?

24:37.643 --> 24:38.644
I love it.

24:40.188 --> 24:44.233
I want to do this one.
Bryan?

24:44.317 --> 24:45.818
It's very different.

24:45.902 --> 24:48.154
I like different.
I'm sick of the same.

24:48.196 --> 24:49.530
I want to do this song.

24:49.614 --> 24:53.493
Yeah.  I'm with Amy on this.

24:53.576 --> 24:56.996
It's a good song.

24:59.081 --> 25:00.708
<i>I'll make
the call.</i>

25:00.791 --> 25:02.585
<i>Rich!
Richard!</i>

25:02.668 --> 25:03.794
Rich! Pick
up the phone!

25:03.878 --> 25:05.140
Right here.

25:05.146 --> 25:06.540
- Get on the phone right now!
- Who is it?

25:06.581 --> 25:09.717
- What are you freaking out about?
- It's Nashville!

25:09.800 --> 25:11.568
The city of Nashville is calling?

25:11.569 --> 25:15.515
No, it's some guy from a record
label that represents Amy Grant.

25:15.598 --> 25:17.850
<i>And he wants to talk to you!</i>

25:17.892 --> 25:19.519
- Did you do this?
- No!

25:19.602 --> 25:21.521
- Was it Gary?
- It wasn't me.

25:21.562 --> 25:23.856
It's Beth. This had to have
been Beth.  Beth!

25:28.152 --> 25:29.779
<i>Just pick
up the phone.</i>

25:29.862 --> 25:30.696
<i>Turn it off.</i>

25:30.780 --> 25:32.031
Hello?

25:32.114 --> 25:33.533
Yes, is this
Rich Mullins?

25:33.574 --> 25:35.243
This is Rich Mullins.

25:35.326 --> 25:37.570
Rich, this is Bryan
Bontrager from Nashville.

25:37.612 --> 25:40.706
What can I do for you
Bryan Bontrager from Nashville?

25:40.748 --> 25:42.492
<i>Rich,</i>

25:42.575 --> 25:46.087
<i>Amy Grant heard your song
Sing Your Praise to the Lord</i>

25:46.170 --> 25:49.131
and she wants to use it
on her next album.

25:49.215 --> 25:53.302
- Who's Amy Grant?
- Are you kidding me?  Oh!

25:53.386 --> 25:55.137
Excuse me?

25:55.221 --> 25:57.557
Shhh.
Sorry about that. Go ahead.

25:57.598 --> 26:00.643
Okay, well, um,
listen, Rich,

26:00.726 --> 26:02.395
we'd like to bring you
down to Nashville

26:02.478 --> 26:04.230
here so we can work
out the writing contract.

26:04.272 --> 26:07.400
Wow, thanks
Bryan, but, uh,

26:07.483 --> 26:09.318
<i>I'm not really
interested.</i>

26:09.402 --> 26:11.988
You're not interested?

26:13.239 --> 26:15.358
<i>Um, look Rich,</i>

26:15.441 --> 26:18.744
I don't think you understand
what we're offering you here, okay?

26:18.828 --> 26:20.955
<i>This is a game changer.</i>

26:21.038 --> 26:23.165
I'm not really sure I want
my game to be changed.

26:23.249 --> 26:25.960
Okay, well, um, Rich,

26:26.043 --> 26:28.754
maybe you should
think about this.

26:28.796 --> 26:31.632
You have a real gift

26:31.716 --> 26:33.009
and maybe you
should be using it.

26:33.092 --> 26:36.012
Well, I think
I am using it.

26:36.095 --> 26:39.348
All right, well, um,

26:39.432 --> 26:42.268
I,uh,hope
you change your mind.

26:42.310 --> 26:44.120
Well, thanks for the call, Bryan.
I appreciate it.

26:44.203 --> 26:45.396
Take care.

26:55.323 --> 26:57.783
What?

27:19.388 --> 27:21.474
<i>When are we going to talk
about the Nashville thing?</i>

27:25.061 --> 27:27.163
We're not going to talk
about the Nashville thing

27:27.246 --> 27:29.398
because I'm not going to Nashville.

27:29.482 --> 27:32.026
You have to go.

27:32.109 --> 27:33.669
Well, are you
coming with me?

27:33.670 --> 27:36.405
You know I can't do that.
We're not even married yet.

27:36.489 --> 27:37.657
What is this?

27:37.740 --> 27:39.533
Is this
your parents?

27:39.617 --> 27:42.244
It's not just
my parents.

27:42.328 --> 27:45.873
You knew
what I wanted.

27:45.956 --> 27:47.375
Your life
is headed

27:47.458 --> 27:49.877
in a totally
different direction.

27:49.960 --> 27:53.422
You don't want to be 41
and stuck in Cincinnati.

27:53.506 --> 27:56.092
Yes, I do.

27:56.175 --> 27:57.843
If you're there,
I do.

28:02.515 --> 28:04.016
You don't belong here.

28:28.207 --> 28:30.876
<i>Hey, Jess,
it's me, uh...</i>

28:30.918 --> 28:32.586
<i>hey, I didn't see you
at the show tonight.</i>

28:32.670 --> 28:34.255
<i>I thought you were
going to be there.</i>

28:34.338 --> 28:35.881
<i>Um...just give
me a call.</i>

29:05.411 --> 29:07.121
<i>I just don't understand</i>

29:07.204 --> 29:08.998
<i>why everything
you touch ends up busted.</i>

29:09.081 --> 29:11.167
<i>Why everything
you touch ends up busted.</i>

29:15.588 --> 29:17.757
<i>Hey, hey, Jess,
it's me.</i>

29:17.840 --> 29:21.677
Listen, call me when you
get this, I just want to talk.

29:21.761 --> 29:25.931
I just, I just feel
like we're not...

29:25.973 --> 29:29.810
I just, I just want to talk about
what's happening with us.

29:29.894 --> 29:32.146
<i>I was just calling to make
sure everything is okay.</i>

29:34.356 --> 29:35.440
<i>I just feel like
we're not connecting</i>

29:35.441 --> 29:37.401
<i>and I don't know...</i>

29:37.443 --> 29:39.779
why we keep
going back and forth

29:39.862 --> 29:41.363
and if there's something
I've done or...

29:47.328 --> 29:50.664
<i>Jess, if the problem is me,
then I just want you to tell me.</i>

30:10.267 --> 30:11.477
Hello?

30:11.560 --> 30:13.687
Hey, Mom.

30:13.771 --> 30:15.314
Are you okay?

30:15.356 --> 30:18.192
I was just missing...
missing you guys.

30:18.275 --> 30:19.819
<i>I just wanted
to say hi.</i>

30:19.860 --> 30:22.822
Neva, I get
up at 4 a.m.

30:22.905 --> 30:24.824
Calm yourself.

30:24.865 --> 30:26.867
Mom, can I talk to
Dad for a second?

30:26.951 --> 30:28.828
Yeah.

30:28.911 --> 30:30.996
Hey, he wants
to talk to you.

30:31.080 --> 30:37.253
Tell that boy to call back at a
decent hour and I'll talk to him.

30:37.336 --> 30:39.171
He said to say
that he loves you

30:39.255 --> 30:41.590
<i>and that
he'll call you later.</i>

30:41.674 --> 30:43.092
He didn't say
that, Mom.

30:43.175 --> 30:45.511
You know your father loves you.

30:45.553 --> 30:47.763
He just has to be at work.

30:47.847 --> 30:50.391
Neva, this is not the time
for his nonsense.

30:50.474 --> 30:53.060
Hang up the damn phone.

30:53.143 --> 30:55.604
<i>He's just tired.</i>

30:55.688 --> 30:58.566
Yeah. Well, sorry
for calling so late.

30:58.649 --> 31:01.026
All right.

31:01.110 --> 31:02.111
Love you.

31:31.140 --> 31:32.391
Hey, Rich.

31:32.433 --> 31:34.059
- Sam.
- Yeah.

31:34.101 --> 31:37.980
Come here.

31:38.063 --> 31:40.065
Where were you?

31:40.149 --> 31:42.818
Have you been drinking?
Answer me!

31:42.902 --> 31:44.403
Gary and I
went to a movie.

31:47.156 --> 31:49.033
Why didn't you
ask me to go?

31:49.116 --> 31:50.618
<i>Dude, I think you
need to sleep it off.</i>

31:50.701 --> 31:51.744
<i>I think you're drunk.</i>

31:51.827 --> 31:52.828
I'm fine.

31:54.413 --> 31:56.790
<i>I take it back.</i>

31:56.874 --> 31:58.751
I know you're drunk.

31:58.834 --> 32:01.128
Sleep it off.

32:04.715 --> 32:05.558
What's this?

32:05.642 --> 32:07.384
It's a camel.
What do you think it is?

32:07.468 --> 32:08.928
It's not a camel.

32:10.346 --> 32:12.348
<i>Sam.</i>

32:12.431 --> 32:14.433
Yeah?

32:14.516 --> 32:16.435
Are we
really friends?

32:20.230 --> 32:22.358
<i>Sam invited me
to come to Wichita</i>

32:22.441 --> 32:25.486
<i>with him to stay with his
folks and sort things out.</i>

32:25.569 --> 32:29.657
<i>The Nashville situation had thrown
a lot of my world out of joint.</i>

32:29.740 --> 32:32.284
<i>I wasn't totally sure
how to put it back.</i>

32:32.326 --> 32:36.455
<i>I think a large part of me worried
that what Jess had said was true.</i>

32:36.538 --> 32:37.790
<i>I had to go.</i>

32:40.292 --> 32:41.460
<i>Rich!</i>

32:43.712 --> 32:46.298
<i>I'll be right back.
We 're out of milk.</i>

32:46.340 --> 32:48.133
Could I talk to you
for a second, Morris?

32:48.175 --> 32:50.844
Yeah.
Absolutely.

32:50.928 --> 32:52.221
What's on your mind?

32:52.304 --> 32:54.890
Oh. Quite a lot.

32:54.974 --> 32:56.517
And Nashville.

32:56.600 --> 32:57.810
Yeah, you heard
about that?

32:57.893 --> 33:00.813
Yeah.
Yeah.

33:00.896 --> 33:02.815
Yeah, Jessie
doesn't want to go

33:02.856 --> 33:05.693
and, um...

33:05.776 --> 33:07.528
she hates the whole idea
of touring but, man,

33:07.611 --> 33:09.363
I don't know how to
do this without her.

33:09.446 --> 33:12.574
You-you want to tour,
do your music.

33:12.658 --> 33:16.495
Yeah, absolutely.  I just
don't want to do it alone.

33:16.578 --> 33:20.165
Yeah.  Well, relationships
are funny that way.

33:20.207 --> 33:23.335
They don't necessarily fix
those kind of problems.

33:23.377 --> 33:26.422
And if you kind of give up
this dream for that dream,

33:26.505 --> 33:28.507
you might lose both of them.

33:28.549 --> 33:31.010
- Hm.
- It sort of happens that way sometimes.

33:31.093 --> 33:34.096
You know why I think
Jesus didn't have a girl?

33:34.179 --> 33:37.099
I am dying to hear
this one. Why?

33:37.182 --> 33:40.019
He didn't have a
home to take her to.

33:40.102 --> 33:42.688
The guy was a Vagabond,
I mean...

33:42.730 --> 33:44.940
The only thing I know is that
Jesus would not like Nashville.

33:45.024 --> 33:48.027
I mean... I just mean
all these cheesy artists

33:48.110 --> 33:50.070
like trying to make a
cheap buck off of his name.

33:50.079 --> 33:52.031
<i>The whole thing makes me
want to puke, to be honest.</i>

33:52.114 --> 33:54.700
Maybe that's why he
wants you to be a part of it.

33:54.742 --> 33:57.286
Yeah.  I don't know if God
needs me to change Nashville.

33:57.369 --> 33:58.954
Oh, I'm sure
he doesn't.

33:59.038 --> 34:02.207
But he still might
want you to be there.

34:02.291 --> 34:04.543
<i>It's just you have
to be careful</i>

34:04.585 --> 34:07.046
<i>thinking that holiness is
about finding the right place</i>

34:07.087 --> 34:09.130
and doing
the right things.

34:09.214 --> 34:11.550
Because it's
really not that.

34:11.632 --> 34:14.469
I mean, holiness
is really about

34:14.553 --> 34:17.139
loving God
in the moment.

34:17.222 --> 34:19.266
<i>I found in my own life
there are a lot of things I know</i>

34:19.349 --> 34:23.145
and there are some
things I don't know.

34:23.228 --> 34:26.065
But if I give it time,

34:26.148 --> 34:28.400
if I really walk
in faith on it,

34:28.484 --> 34:30.485
I don't have
answers to everything,

34:30.569 --> 34:33.739
but I've been amazed
at the things I found out.

34:33.781 --> 34:35.657
And the thing I know about it,

34:35.741 --> 34:37.659
is that God loves you
no matter what you choose.

34:37.743 --> 34:39.828
And he's
going to be there.

34:39.911 --> 34:42.748
He's going to be there
with you on this journey.

34:42.790 --> 34:44.583
All right. So what
about the girl?

34:44.625 --> 34:46.793
Yeah.

34:46.877 --> 34:48.670
Well, I don't know
everything about women...

34:51.215 --> 34:55.677
But I have been married to
one woman for almost 20 years.

34:55.761 --> 34:58.347
And the reason that
works is because

34:58.430 --> 35:01.475
she says, "Go get milk"
and I go get milk.

35:01.558 --> 35:03.519
And then I pick
up ice cream.

35:03.602 --> 35:06.522
Ooh, I hear you.

35:06.605 --> 35:08.190
Rocky Road.

35:08.273 --> 35:09.858
There is
no other kind.

35:11.143 --> 35:12.470
- I'll be right back.
- Thanks, Morris.

35:12.478 --> 35:13.862
All right, I'll see you.

35:19.409 --> 35:21.286
He still not here?

35:21.370 --> 35:23.372
He'll be here.

35:23.455 --> 35:26.625
I want to make sure we get
a few things clear before I go on.

35:26.708 --> 35:29.350
Hey man, we've done this before.
It's going to be okay.

35:29.353 --> 35:31.463
Not in my church.

35:31.505 --> 35:35.217
First off, you boys all better
find yourselves some shoes.

35:35.300 --> 35:36.885
This is a house of God.

35:36.969 --> 35:39.471
And clean up,
tuck your shirt tail in,

35:39.513 --> 35:41.723
have some self respect.

35:41.807 --> 35:44.893
I'm going to be talking
today about being holy,

35:44.977 --> 35:47.396
being disciplined,
and shaping up.

35:47.479 --> 35:49.148
And I want you
to play something

35:49.189 --> 35:51.650
that will really drive
that message home.

35:51.733 --> 35:53.490
You understand?

35:53.494 --> 35:55.904
And I hope you'll be out
there listening to my sermon.

35:59.616 --> 36:01.869
So, Gary, do you
want to tell Richard?

36:01.952 --> 36:05.414
<i>If you're going to get
serious about your faith,</i>

36:05.497 --> 36:08.500
you need to look at
this book like a rule book.

36:08.542 --> 36:12.754
It has the dos
and the don'ts.

36:12.838 --> 36:15.257
<i>Are you going
to follow the dos?</i>

36:15.340 --> 36:17.926
<i>Or you choose the don'ts?</i>

36:18.010 --> 36:20.721
As Zion comes up
to close us in song,

36:20.804 --> 36:23.724
I want to leave you
with this question.

36:23.807 --> 36:25.434
Would Christ
be proud of you?

36:42.034 --> 36:47.207
Yeah, I don't want to be disrespectful.
I know we're guests here, but...

36:48.248 --> 36:50.792
I kind of think how
disrespectful it would be

36:50.876 --> 36:54.129
not be honest with the church.

36:54.213 --> 36:57.299
<i>I think it was
the theologian Karl Barth</i>

36:57.382 --> 37:00.302
who was asked once
what's the most...

37:00.385 --> 37:05.474
What's the most theologically
profound statement

37:05.557 --> 37:09.311
and this is
how he responded.

37:09.394 --> 37:14.399
♪ Jesus loves me this I know ♪

37:17.069 --> 37:22.658
♪ For the Bible tells me so ♪

37:24.284 --> 37:29.623
♪ They're the ones to Him belong ♪

37:29.706 --> 37:35.671
♪ They are weak but he is strong ♪

37:37.005 --> 37:42.636
♪ Yes, Jesus loves me ♪

37:42.719 --> 37:47.266
♪ Yes, Jesus
loves me ♪

37:49.101 --> 37:54.523
♪ Yes, Jesus loves me ♪

37:54.606 --> 37:59.361
♪ The Bible tells me so ♪

38:05.284 --> 38:09.454
Whenever I hear people say
that Christians are hypocrites,

38:09.538 --> 38:11.707
I kind of go, "Man, every
time we get together

38:11.790 --> 38:14.126
we're confessing
that we're hypocrites."

38:16.795 --> 38:18.714
The need of God and
the need of each other,

38:23.635 --> 38:25.220
it's all the pretending
to be perfect

38:25.304 --> 38:30.642
that breeds
inauthenticity in the church.

38:30.726 --> 38:34.187
Because none of us are.

38:36.565 --> 38:41.069
I've been wrestling lately
with-with surrender myself.

38:45.741 --> 38:47.326
But He loves us still.

38:58.503 --> 39:01.006
I think I need
to go to Nashville.

39:05.761 --> 39:10.432
Whether I go
or whether I don't go,

39:10.515 --> 39:12.392
I kind of think
it doesn't matter.

39:15.354 --> 39:17.773
Because in the end
all that really matters,

39:22.027 --> 39:27.449
♪ Yes, Jesus loves me ♪

39:27.532 --> 39:32.037
♪ Yes, Jesus
loves me ♪

39:33.663 --> 39:38.794
♪ Yes, Jesus loves me ♪

39:38.877 --> 39:43.799
♪ The Bible tells me so ♪

39:46.968 --> 39:50.097
Nashville is so
not ready for him.

39:50.180 --> 39:51.473
I know.

39:53.683 --> 39:56.311
Hey!

39:56.395 --> 39:59.272
You weren't going to go without
saying goodbye to me, were you?

40:03.735 --> 40:04.945
Miss me.

40:05.028 --> 40:08.073
Yeah.
Of course I will.

40:08.156 --> 40:09.825
You're the one that
got me into this mess,

40:09.908 --> 40:11.410
this whole
Nashville thing.

40:13.912 --> 40:17.541
You just don't want
to go without Jess, so...

40:17.624 --> 40:19.668
quit being
a chicken, right?

40:24.714 --> 40:26.842
Just don't forget
about us, okay?

40:32.222 --> 40:33.140
<i>Richard!</i>

40:34.641 --> 40:37.185
Hey. I got to go
but don't forget

40:37.269 --> 40:38.395
who your real
friends are.

40:40.063 --> 40:41.064
<i>I'll miss you.</i>

40:43.900 --> 40:45.235
Time to go.

40:49.489 --> 40:50.490
You Okay?

40:54.453 --> 40:57.372
She's right.

40:57.456 --> 41:00.625
I am
so scared.

41:00.709 --> 41:04.963
It'll be okay.  We're
only five hours away.

41:05.046 --> 41:06.715
I'm doing what He
wants me to do.

41:06.798 --> 41:10.051
You'd think this would
be easier or something.

41:10.135 --> 41:12.137
If you're really
so scared about going,

41:12.220 --> 41:13.329
why don't you
move this junk

41:13.330 --> 41:15.250
and I'll ride with you
to the edge of town.

41:15.257 --> 41:16.600
Let me get my wallet.

41:20.479 --> 41:21.563
<i>Hey. hey!</i>

41:22.814 --> 41:25.066
<i>Hey, uh...</i>

41:25.150 --> 41:28.153
I think you packed
up some of my shirts.

41:31.031 --> 41:32.991
<i>Leaving Cincinnati
for Nashville</i>

41:33.074 --> 41:36.077
<i>was one of the hardest
things I've ever done.</i>

41:36.161 --> 41:42.042
<i>I felt like I was trading
one life for another.</i>

41:42.125 --> 41:43.877
<i>But I couldn't shake
the feeling</i>

41:43.960 --> 41:45.212
<i>that God wanted me
there for some reason.</i>

41:54.888 --> 41:58.183
<i>It was a whirlwind
from the time I arrived.</i>

41:58.225 --> 42:00.435
<i>Sing Your Praise to the Lord
was a big hit for Amy</i>

42:00.519 --> 42:02.437
<i>and her album became
the biggest selling album</i>

42:02.521 --> 42:04.606
<i>in Christian radio
at the time so</i>

42:04.689 --> 42:07.859
<i>so of course they wanted
me to write more songs.</i>

42:07.943 --> 42:09.736
<i>As much as I
enjoyed writing music,</i>

42:09.737 --> 42:16.201
<i>I felt more and more that
I wanted to record my own work.</i>

42:16.284 --> 42:20.372
<i>I had meetings with publishers
but without much luck and...</i>

42:20.455 --> 42:21.690
<i>I'm not sure I fit</i>

42:21.699 --> 42:24.793
<i>the aesthetic of
contemporary Christian music.</i>

42:24.876 --> 42:27.128
<i>Besides, songwriting and
royalties gave me something</i>

42:27.212 --> 42:30.882
<i>I'd never had before,
which was a steady income.</i>

42:30.966 --> 42:32.717
<i>Not that I entirely knew
what to do with it.</i>

42:38.223 --> 42:40.308
<i>All the money in Nashville
couldn't change the fact</i>

42:40.392 --> 42:42.811
<i>that I missed
my friends back home.</i>

42:42.894 --> 42:44.771
<i>Especially Jess.</i>

43:06.710 --> 43:09.963
♪ You find a love that's tender ♪

43:10.046 --> 43:13.174
♪ If you find someone that's true ♪

43:13.258 --> 43:15.302
♪ Thank the Lord ♪

43:15.385 --> 43:18.013
♪ He's been doubly good to you ♪

43:21.975 --> 43:23.810
That's beautiful.

43:23.893 --> 43:25.854
You doing okay?

43:25.937 --> 43:27.439
Got into another fight
with Matt and Bryan.

43:27.522 --> 43:29.608
Another one, huh?

43:29.649 --> 43:31.443
This one was messy.

43:31.484 --> 43:33.987
You sure don't like to
play by the rules, do you?

43:34.070 --> 43:36.781
Amy, I don't even know
what the rules are.

43:36.823 --> 43:39.200
I've been here for a while now,
I've been writing for a while,

43:39.284 --> 43:41.661
don't get me wrong,
I like writing for you and...

43:41.745 --> 43:44.706
I like writing
for people but...

43:44.789 --> 43:46.374
I want to record
my own stuff.

43:46.458 --> 43:48.460
And they won't
even hear me out.

43:48.501 --> 43:50.019
So why don't they?

43:50.020 --> 43:51.921
I mean, they're keeping
me out of the loop on this.

43:52.005 --> 43:55.342
They say my songs
are too dark or too...

43:55.425 --> 43:59.846
I don't know, not happy enough,
not cheery and cheesy, if you ask me.

43:59.929 --> 44:03.224
What were you playing
when I walked in?

44:03.308 --> 44:04.476
Did you like it?

44:04.559 --> 44:06.311
Yeah.
Did you really?

44:06.394 --> 44:08.521
Yeah.
Really really?

44:09.898 --> 44:12.984
I loved it.
What is it?

44:13.068 --> 44:15.904
It's a song I wrote
for my wedding.

44:15.987 --> 44:18.156
Can you play me
the rest of the song?

44:18.198 --> 44:20.241
Yeah.

44:20.325 --> 44:21.409
Sure.

44:21.493 --> 44:23.161
It's just a chorus.

44:25.664 --> 44:30.502
♪   You can thank the Father   ♪
for the things that He has done

44:32.796 --> 44:36.716
♪   Thank him for the   ♪
things He's yet to do

44:38.385 --> 44:42.013
♪    If you find    ♪
a love that's tender

44:42.055 --> 44:45.100
♪ If you find someone who's true ♪

44:45.183 --> 44:47.102
♪ Thank the Lord ♪

44:47.185 --> 44:49.771
♪ He's been doubly good to you ♪

44:51.690 --> 44:53.775
Rich, seriously you have
to give me that song.

44:53.858 --> 44:56.027
I want that song.

44:56.111 --> 44:57.195
Sorry.

44:59.239 --> 45:02.033
That one's for the girl.

45:48.121 --> 45:52.417
You know, I'm being asked
by people all the time

45:52.500 --> 45:54.085
how do you feel
close to God.

45:54.127 --> 45:56.463
And I kind of go

45:56.546 --> 45:59.090
"You know what?
I don't really know that."

45:59.174 --> 46:02.927
When I think about the
lives of...of the great saints

46:03.011 --> 46:08.767
I don't necessarily think that
they always felt close to God.

46:08.808 --> 46:11.102
See, closeness to God,
it isn't about feelings.

46:11.144 --> 46:15.106
Closeness to God
is about obedience.

46:15.148 --> 46:18.818
But if we don't obey,
we don't even have a chance.

46:27.786 --> 46:29.287
What's up, bud?

46:29.329 --> 46:31.664
Hey, Rich.

46:31.748 --> 46:33.208
That was
a really good show.

46:33.291 --> 46:36.211
Thanks.
It was fun.

46:36.294 --> 46:38.963
Can I talk
to you for a second?

46:39.047 --> 46:40.632
Yeah.
Absolutely.

46:40.673 --> 46:41.966
<i>What's up?</i>

46:42.050 --> 46:43.468
No, it's just...
I just

46:43.551 --> 46:47.096
want to say thank you

46:47.180 --> 46:48.264
for what you
said in there.

46:48.348 --> 46:51.309
Yeah, you bet, man.

46:51.351 --> 46:53.645
What did I say exactly?

46:53.728 --> 46:54.979
You said a lot.

46:55.063 --> 46:56.481
' -1

46:56.564 --> 46:59.359
- I'm not feeling close to God.
- Hm.

46:59.442 --> 47:04.531
It's just that I struggle
a lot with loneliness.

47:04.614 --> 47:06.366
I'm going to fill you
in on a little secret

47:06.449 --> 47:07.909
<i>that they won't tell
you in Sunday School.</i>

47:07.992 --> 47:09.410
<i>All the heroes
in the Bible,</i>

47:09.494 --> 47:12.372
all the weirdos
in the Bible,

47:12.455 --> 47:14.541
they all struggled
with the same stuff.

47:14.624 --> 47:17.544
Loneliness and all of it.

47:17.627 --> 47:22.507
It's just that some of us
aren't afraid to admit it.

47:25.009 --> 47:27.053
You know?

47:27.136 --> 47:28.888
<i>Yeah.</i>

47:28.972 --> 47:31.224
It's my dad.
I've got to go.

47:31.307 --> 47:33.518
<i>I won't forget.
Thanks, Rich.</i>

47:33.560 --> 47:35.520
You bet, man.
Nice to meet you.

47:35.603 --> 47:37.188
<i>Good night.
Good night.</i>

47:42.861 --> 47:44.404
<i>Every small conversation</i>

47:44.487 --> 47:46.447
<i>or fleeting moment
of connection</i>

47:46.531 --> 47:49.117
<i>reminded me that despite
all the flaws and tackiness</i>

47:49.200 --> 47:50.952
<i>of the Christian
music industry,</i>

47:51.035 --> 47:53.246
<i>God had given me
something to say</i>

47:53.329 --> 47:55.456
<i>and a platform
to share it.</i>

47:55.540 --> 48:00.545
<i>I realized that music could
be more than just music.</i>

48:00.628 --> 48:03.798
<i>But they didn't let me start
just making records over night.</i>

48:03.882 --> 48:06.092
<i>It took some convincing.</i>

48:06.175 --> 48:07.530
<i>Did you read the letter?</i>

48:07.536 --> 48:09.980
<i>- I haven't had time.
- Matt, this is important.</i>

48:09.988 --> 48:11.806
Can you at least tell
me you'll read it today?

48:11.890 --> 48:14.225
Just tell me,
what is it?

48:14.309 --> 48:16.477
I want to talk to you about
me recording my own songs.

48:16.661 --> 48:19.004
Rich, you know I think
you're an amazing writer,

48:19.005 --> 48:21.357
but I don't think you're
ready to be a recording artist.

48:21.441 --> 48:24.235
Sorry, we'll just talk
about this later, okay?

48:24.319 --> 48:26.154
What?
When I'm ready, Matt?

48:26.237 --> 48:27.739
What's with you, Rich?

48:27.822 --> 48:29.270
Do you really want
to do this here?

48:29.274 --> 48:31.284
- In front of Amy...
- I have the right to know!

48:31.367 --> 48:33.244
Look, you really want
to be a recording artist?

48:33.328 --> 48:34.728
Then everything's
got to change.

48:34.729 --> 48:36.623
Your look,
the way you dress,

48:36.706 --> 48:39.334
- it's your stage presence...
- What about my songs?

48:39.417 --> 48:41.127
I don't think
they're ready either.

48:48.343 --> 48:50.845
♪ This life has shown me ♪

48:50.929 --> 48:53.723
♪  How we're mended  ♪
and how we're torn

48:55.391 --> 48:57.352
♪ How it's okay to be lonely ♪

48:57.435 --> 49:01.773
♪ As long as you're free ♪

49:01.856 --> 49:05.193
♪   But sometimes   ♪
my ground was stony

49:05.276 --> 49:08.821
♪    And sometimes    ♪
covered up with thorns

49:08.905 --> 49:15.453
♪ Only you could make it ♪
what it had to be

49:16.921 --> 49:18.998
♪ If they dressed me ♪
like a pauper

49:19.082 --> 49:23.127
♪ Or if they dined me ♪
like a prince

49:23.169 --> 49:25.880
♪ If they lay me with my fathers ♪

49:25.964 --> 49:29.951
♪ Or with my ashes scattered ♪
on the wind I don't care

49:30.034 --> 49:35.848
♪   Because when I leave   ♪
I want to go out like Elijah

49:35.932 --> 49:42.814
♪    With a whirlwind    ♪
to fuel my chariot of fire

49:42.897 --> 49:46.109
♪   And when I look   ♪
back on the stars

49:46.192 --> 49:50.071
♪ It'll be like a candle light ♪
on Central Park

49:52.448 --> 49:56.828
♪    It won't break    ♪
my heart to say goodbye

50:11.592 --> 50:13.428
He seems ready to me.

50:18.641 --> 50:20.560
<i>Eventually, the label
gave me a shot</i>

50:20.643 --> 50:23.271
<i>and they signed me
to a pretty modest contract</i>

50:23.354 --> 50:25.356
<i>After a few months,
I finished my first album</i>

50:25.440 --> 50:28.568
called, well,
Rich Mullins.

50:30.737 --> 50:32.238
<i>After that,
I went on tour with Amy</i>

50:32.321 --> 50:33.823
<i>and opened
at her concerts.</i>

50:37.160 --> 50:39.037
<i>I found
that being on the road</i>

50:39.120 --> 50:41.539
<i>was much more enjoyable
than being in the studio.</i>

50:41.622 --> 50:44.959
<i>Maybe it's because I didn't like
Nashville very much, I don't know.</i>

50:45.043 --> 50:47.712
<i>Music was always something
that was a part of me,</i>

50:47.754 --> 50:49.170
<i>something I needed to share.</i>

50:49.173 --> 50:52.383
<i>Now I was reaching so many
people every night, it was exciting,</i>

50:52.467 --> 50:56.178
<i>despite all the corporate
politics that went with it.</i>

50:56.179 --> 50:59.490
<i>But it's funny how you can meet
hundreds of new people every day.</i>

50:59.491 --> 51:01.025
<i>Thank you, thank you.</i>

51:01.026 --> 51:03.478
<i>And still feel
almost completely alone.</i>

51:03.561 --> 51:05.313
<i>Thank you all
so much.</i>

51:05.396 --> 51:07.023
<i>We're going to take
a real quick break now</i>

51:07.106 --> 51:08.399
<i>and be right back
in a few minutes.</i>

51:18.659 --> 51:20.495
There he is!

51:20.578 --> 51:22.112
Tell us!
Here's our rock star!

51:22.113 --> 51:24.270
She does that so way
better than you, man.

51:24.273 --> 51:26.000
Yeah, she's
really talented.

51:26.084 --> 51:27.585
How are you feeling?

51:27.668 --> 51:29.087
Ah. Okay, let's go,
let's go, let's go.

51:29.170 --> 51:31.172
Who's smoking?

51:31.255 --> 51:35.802
- Hey.
- Ohhh. So proud of you.

51:37.970 --> 51:40.098
- Wayne.
- Hey,Dad.

51:40.181 --> 51:41.790
You look like a girl
with that long hair.

51:41.791 --> 51:43.101
You need a hair cut, boy.

51:46.104 --> 51:49.315
You haven't seen me in months
and that's what you have to say?

51:49.398 --> 51:50.775
It's only a joke.

51:50.817 --> 51:52.527
Don't be
so damn sensitive.

51:52.610 --> 51:54.378
I guess piano players
can wear their hair

51:54.462 --> 51:56.688
however they want
these days.

51:56.689 --> 51:59.467
Rich, would you mind coming back on
at the end and doing the rain thing?

51:59.468 --> 52:00.567
Absolutely.

52:00.568 --> 52:02.703
You've got
a very talented son here.

52:02.787 --> 52:04.372
You must be
a very proud father.

52:04.455 --> 52:06.124
No, I'm proud
of all my kids.

52:06.165 --> 52:07.375
Two boys,
two girls,

52:07.458 --> 52:09.544
and a...piano player.

52:11.129 --> 52:12.130
I got to go.

52:23.558 --> 52:26.227
What we're going to do,

52:26.310 --> 52:28.178
we're going to make rain, okay?

52:28.179 --> 52:30.523
So what I'm going to do is break
you guys up into three groups.

52:32.066 --> 52:33.317
This one's about here.

52:35.403 --> 52:36.654
<i>Nice.</i>

53:30.208 --> 53:31.876
Come on,
pick up.

53:33.753 --> 53:35.254
<i>Hello?</i>

53:35.338 --> 53:36.797
Jess!

53:36.881 --> 53:38.549
<i>Oh.
It's me.</i>

53:38.591 --> 53:40.468
<i>Hey, Richard.
Sorry I didn't make it.</i>

53:40.551 --> 53:44.222
Oh, no,
that's fine.

53:44.305 --> 53:46.140
Hey, listen, what are you
doing next weekend?

53:46.224 --> 53:47.642
The tour is coming
through Cincinnati...

53:47.725 --> 53:49.060
<i>Rich, I'm engaged.</i>

53:51.062 --> 53:52.370
<i>I'm sorry.</i>

53:52.372 --> 53:56.150
<i>I just, I don't know,
I just...</i>

53:56.234 --> 53:57.610
<i>I thought
you should know.</i>

54:20.174 --> 54:25.763
<i>You know,
I'm not a real...</i>

54:25.846 --> 54:28.599
<i>I don't know...</i>

54:28.641 --> 54:32.979
<i>I have no interest
in anybody else.</i>

54:33.062 --> 54:36.816
<i>The woman I'm in love with
is married to someone else so...</i>

54:36.899 --> 54:39.443
<i>that's the way it...</i>

54:39.527 --> 54:41.779
<i>that's the way it goes,</i>

54:41.821 --> 54:42.822
<i>and I don't mind that.</i>

54:46.158 --> 54:49.954
I think maybe God
wanted me to be celibate.

54:50.037 --> 54:53.082
The way he accomplished
that was to break my heart.

54:54.750 --> 54:56.502
So the song
you wrote for your wedding,

54:56.585 --> 55:02.008
<i>Doubly Good,
you gave to Amy Grant. Why?</i>

55:02.091 --> 55:05.288
Some things you just have
to walk away from, you know.

55:05.504 --> 55:08.830
And some things
you don't have a choice.

55:08.831 --> 55:12.743
The woman I love is married to
somebody else. That's the way it goes.

55:14.603 --> 55:16.480
Well, if that's the case,
then it seems to me

55:16.564 --> 55:19.150
that song
is exceptionally cruel.

55:19.191 --> 55:21.068
<i>Why is that?</i>

55:21.152 --> 55:24.255
Well, because it implies
that if God hasn't given you

55:24.338 --> 55:26.240
a love that's tender
and someone who's true

55:26.324 --> 55:29.827
<i>then he hasn't been
doubly good to you.</i>

55:29.869 --> 55:32.830
Well, God doesn't have to be
singly good to any of us.

55:32.872 --> 55:35.666
<i>We all have it better
than we deserve so...</i>

55:35.708 --> 55:37.835
<i>we should be thankful
for what we have.</i>

58:04.148 --> 58:05.524
It's good.

58:05.608 --> 58:06.817
<i>That's horrible.</i>

58:06.859 --> 58:08.819
I like it.
Bryan?

58:08.903 --> 58:10.404
<i>Maybe if we
just changed...</i>

58:10.488 --> 58:11.697
No, I don't want to...

58:11.780 --> 58:13.157
I don't want to change...

58:13.199 --> 58:15.826
I don't want
to do it at all.

58:15.910 --> 58:19.163
Okay this song is... it's exactly this that
made me not want to come to Nashville.

58:19.246 --> 58:22.249
Yeah, you made
that clear, Mullins.

58:22.333 --> 58:24.710
But no one's holding
a gun to your head here.

58:24.793 --> 58:26.003
We're just trying to help.

58:26.045 --> 58:28.547
Well, you're not helping.

58:28.631 --> 58:30.670
Look, my songs aren't
fill-in-the-blanks, you guys.

58:30.675 --> 58:33.844
You can't just put the word "Jesus" in a
few more times and expect it to be better.

58:33.928 --> 58:36.680
Rich, you already have a
lot of longing and brokenness

58:36.722 --> 58:38.390
in your other songs,
which is good.

58:38.474 --> 58:40.726
Maybe if you
just had happier lyrics.

58:40.809 --> 58:43.229
I'm not trying to be
a Christian pop star, guys.

58:43.312 --> 58:46.106
I'm just trying to say something true.
Okay?

58:46.190 --> 58:48.526
I don't want to
change my music.

58:48.609 --> 58:52.571
Yeah?
Well, things change.

58:52.655 --> 58:56.116
You sure don't seem
to mind a new car,

58:56.200 --> 58:58.285
a new house, right?

58:58.369 --> 58:59.910
Don't mess with my songs.

58:59.912 --> 59:02.540
Rich, we don't want to mess
with your songs, okay?

59:02.623 --> 59:05.125
But in order for people
to hear your music,

59:05.209 --> 59:06.590
we have to sell records.

59:06.594 --> 59:08.587
And in order
to sell records,

59:08.671 --> 59:10.430
- we have to get the sound right.
- Yeah!

59:10.431 --> 59:12.550
The problem is the sound.
The problem is me.  I got it.

59:12.633 --> 59:14.426
I get it.

59:14.510 --> 59:16.887
What are you doing?

59:16.929 --> 59:18.989
You can't leave, we're in
the middle of a session!

59:18.990 --> 59:21.520
<i>You don't want to hear anything
I have to say to you right now.</i>

59:24.687 --> 59:27.940
He's never going
to sing this song.

59:28.023 --> 59:29.775
Well, if he
doesn't sing this one,

59:29.858 --> 59:31.485
he's going to have to come
up with something else.

59:31.569 --> 59:33.404
We still got
one more slot to fill.

59:39.827 --> 59:43.589
You know, he has more talent
than anyone I've ever seen.

59:46.375 --> 59:49.920
What if he never gets
off the ground?

01:00:09.231 --> 01:00:10.515
Hello?

01:00:10.516 --> 01:00:11.398
<i>Hey, Rich.</i>

01:00:11.451 --> 01:00:12.611
Hey, Gary.
What's up, man?

01:00:12.686 --> 01:00:15.210
<i>I know you're slammed,
but I got a friend</i>

01:00:15.213 --> 01:00:16.467
<i>who's asking for a favor.</i>

01:00:16.481 --> 01:00:18.138
<i>Would you have
time to do a show?</i>

01:00:18.183 --> 01:00:20.365
Man, I don't know.  We're
kind of behind on this thing.

01:00:20.368 --> 01:00:21.869
The labels all over me about it.

01:00:21.870 --> 01:00:24.821
<i>- It's on a Native American reservation.
- Really?</i>

01:00:24.822 --> 01:00:28.000
<i>Yeah, but it's all
the way out in Arizona.</i>

01:00:28.083 --> 01:00:31.462
<i>It's, like, you know, a
million miles from Nashville.</i>

01:00:31.545 --> 01:00:34.882
