01:17:35.735 --> 01:17:37.528
You remember me?
Yeah, absolutely.

01:17:37.612 --> 01:17:39.405
- I hope you don't mind I got...
- No, not at all.

01:17:39.489 --> 01:17:41.115
You kind of picked
the worst possible time.

01:17:41.199 --> 01:17:42.659
I'm literally just getting
ready to leave

01:17:42.742 --> 01:17:44.160
but if you need
a place to crash

01:17:44.202 --> 01:17:45.870
you know, it's yours.

01:17:45.953 --> 01:17:47.330
Where are you going?

01:17:47.413 --> 01:17:49.666
I'm moving
to Wichita, actually.

01:17:49.707 --> 01:17:51.417
Oh.

01:17:51.501 --> 01:17:53.378
What are you doing
in Nashville anyway?

01:17:53.461 --> 01:17:56.547
Looking for a job.

01:17:56.631 --> 01:17:59.591
I'll tell you what, if you want a crappy
job, you can come join the band.

01:17:59.592 --> 01:18:00.300
Really?

01:18:00.301 --> 01:18:02.095
Yeah.
Sure, why not?

01:18:02.178 --> 01:18:04.013
- You're just going to let me join the band?
- Yeah!

01:18:04.055 --> 01:18:05.765
- Awesome.
- Come in.

01:18:05.848 --> 01:18:07.350
Let's get this crappy job started.

01:18:07.433 --> 01:18:08.768
Here, take that
to the jeep, will you?

01:18:12.939 --> 01:18:14.857
<i>It turns out Justin
is just as broken as I was</i>

01:18:14.899 --> 01:18:17.860
<i>when he landed
on my doorstep.</i>

01:18:17.902 --> 01:18:20.196
<i>That was one of the many
things we had in common.</i>

01:18:20.238 --> 01:18:23.449
<i>Along with enjoying
Aaron Copeland and road trips</i>

01:18:23.533 --> 01:18:25.118
<i>broken relationships
with our fathers,</i>

01:18:25.201 --> 01:18:27.120
<i>and greasy truck stop food,</i>

01:18:27.203 --> 01:18:29.122
<i>stale motel lobby coffee,</i>

01:18:29.205 --> 01:18:31.374
<i>it goes on and on.</i>

01:18:31.457 --> 01:18:33.543
<i>And more than anything,</i>

01:18:33.626 --> 01:18:35.294
<i>if was just nice to have
a friend on the road.</i>

01:18:35.378 --> 01:18:37.296
So what?  You want
to be like Saint Frank?

01:18:37.380 --> 01:18:41.926
It's not about being like
Saint Francis necessarily,

01:18:42.009 --> 01:18:43.386
it's about following Jesus,

01:18:43.469 --> 01:18:44.804
it's about being
like Christ.

01:18:44.887 --> 01:18:47.390
I mean,
how do you do that?

01:18:47.432 --> 01:18:48.891
I'm not good
at being perfect.

01:18:48.975 --> 01:18:51.894
But it's
not about being perfect.

01:18:51.978 --> 01:18:53.980
Look at Saint Francis.

01:18:54.063 --> 01:18:55.815
He took vows.
He took a vow of chastity,

01:18:55.898 --> 01:18:58.109
he took a vow of poverty,

01:18:58.192 --> 01:18:59.736
a vow of obedience.

01:18:59.819 --> 01:19:01.738
I think that's what
we're really missing.

01:19:01.821 --> 01:19:05.825
That's what I want to do.

01:19:05.908 --> 01:19:07.493
I think
I want to start living

01:19:07.577 --> 01:19:09.412
on whatever
the average American salary is.

01:19:09.454 --> 01:19:12.248
Whatever the average
American worker makes.

01:19:12.331 --> 01:19:14.083
Says the man
making millions.

01:19:14.167 --> 01:19:16.252
Who cares?

01:19:16.335 --> 01:19:18.963
Money destroys
people, man.

01:19:19.046 --> 01:19:20.965
Money doesn't have
to destroy people.

01:19:23.926 --> 01:19:25.344
Well, it's destroying me.

01:19:34.020 --> 01:19:36.022
<i>You moved
to Wichita, Kansas</i>

01:19:36.105 --> 01:19:39.108
<i>to go back to college
at Friends University</i>

01:19:39.150 --> 01:19:41.027
<i>and do I have this right</i>

01:19:41.110 --> 01:19:43.321
<i>that you went to get
a music education degree?</i>

01:19:43.404 --> 01:19:45.114
No, I mean, yeah.

01:19:45.198 --> 01:19:46.949
It's true that I went
to get a music degree.

01:19:46.991 --> 01:19:49.118
<i>I wanted
to be able to teach kids</i>

01:19:49.202 --> 01:19:51.621
<i>but the real reason I went
back to Wichita was Morris.</i>

01:19:57.543 --> 01:20:03.341
<i>I thought maybe being around him
would make me walk a little straighter.</i>

01:20:03.424 --> 01:20:05.176
<i>To be honest, it's
the closest thing to home</i>

01:20:05.259 --> 01:20:06.928
I've found
in a long, long time.

01:20:29.492 --> 01:20:30.535
What' up, man?
I'm Rich.

01:20:30.618 --> 01:20:32.203
Hey, I'm Mitch.

01:20:32.286 --> 01:20:33.329
<i>Nice to meet you.
Nice to meet you.</i>

01:20:33.371 --> 01:20:34.831
Nice guitar.

01:20:34.914 --> 01:20:36.582
Yeah.
Thanks.

01:20:36.666 --> 01:20:37.667
I'm just starting out.

01:20:37.750 --> 01:20:39.335
Sweet.

01:20:39.418 --> 01:20:41.379
This is James
Bryan Smith's class, right?

01:20:41.462 --> 01:20:43.506
Yeah.  What, you
weren't here last week?

01:20:43.548 --> 01:20:45.341
No, no, I was bummed.
I had to miss it.

01:20:45.383 --> 01:20:47.718
I was actually in Ireland.

01:20:47.802 --> 01:20:51.180
And Ireland's incredible so I wasn't
really that bummed to be honest but...

01:20:51.264 --> 01:20:54.559
<i>Yeah. You're seeing
friends, family?</i>

01:20:54.642 --> 01:20:57.854
Actually I was shooting
a music video.

01:20:57.937 --> 01:20:59.960
It's not as cool
as it seems.

01:20:59.964 --> 01:21:00.973
Hey, everyone.

01:21:00.974 --> 01:21:03.006
Glad to see you all made
it back to class.

01:21:05.528 --> 01:21:07.113
Can I help you?

01:21:07.196 --> 01:21:10.366
- This is Intro to Religion, right?
- Yes.

01:21:10.408 --> 01:21:12.410
What's your name?
Do you have a student ID?

01:21:12.493 --> 01:21:14.036
Uh, my name
is Rich Mullins.

01:21:14.120 --> 01:21:16.873
I'm not sure
about the student ID.

01:21:16.956 --> 01:21:18.374
The Rich Mullins?

01:21:18.457 --> 01:21:19.959
<i>Awesome God guy.</i>

01:21:20.042 --> 01:21:21.961
I do have other songs.

01:21:22.044 --> 01:21:24.463
All right, and you're
taking this class?

01:21:24.547 --> 01:21:26.215
<i>Yeah.</i>

01:21:26.299 --> 01:21:27.716
Why?

01:21:27.717 --> 01:21:29.844
Actually, I was hoping you
would tell me that part.

01:21:29.927 --> 01:21:31.721
Okay, sorry.

01:21:31.804 --> 01:21:33.539
Glad to have you, Rich.

01:21:33.540 --> 01:21:38.352
Everyone, take out your copies of G.K.
Chesterton's Orthodoxy.

01:21:55.786 --> 01:21:57.413
Good morning.

01:21:57.455 --> 01:21:59.916
Yes, it is.
Barely.

01:22:01.918 --> 01:22:03.753
I think this is the earliest
I've seen you, man.

01:22:03.836 --> 01:22:05.338
Good job.

01:22:05.421 --> 01:22:08.007
That's funny.
Justin up?

01:22:08.090 --> 01:22:09.926
<i>Well, I haven't seen him
down by the coffee pot</i>

01:22:10.009 --> 01:22:13.137
<i>so chances are
he's not up yet.</i>

01:22:13.220 --> 01:22:14.931
Sam called.
Oh, yeah?

01:22:15.014 --> 01:22:16.974
<i>Said hi, yeah.</i>

01:22:17.058 --> 01:22:19.602
Does he, uh, got the beard
going these days?

01:22:19.644 --> 01:22:21.270
Uh, no.
He's on a diet.

01:22:26.943 --> 01:22:28.402
So you call
your dad yet?

01:22:33.366 --> 01:22:37.536
Why should I, Morris?

01:22:37.620 --> 01:22:42.124
I don't know the history
between you guys...

01:22:42.166 --> 01:22:45.127
but if you're blessed enough
to have a dad to call,

01:22:45.211 --> 01:22:47.505
<i>you should call him.</i>

01:22:47.588 --> 01:22:51.634
You've been more of a father to me
these last three months.

01:22:51.676 --> 01:22:53.386
Yeah, but I'm
not your dad.

01:22:53.469 --> 01:22:56.222
I am your friend.

01:22:56.305 --> 01:22:58.724
And as your friend,
I'm telling you...

01:22:58.808 --> 01:22:59.809
<i>Call your dad.</i>

01:23:29.005 --> 01:23:30.339
Morris, you okay?

01:23:31.632 --> 01:23:33.092
<i>Morris!</i>

01:23:33.175 --> 01:23:34.626
Hey, hey, hey, hey!
Hey, Morris!

01:23:34.627 --> 01:23:37.221
Morris!  Hey, talk to me,
buddy.  Talk to me.

01:23:37.304 --> 01:23:39.515
Morris!

01:23:39.557 --> 01:23:41.017
Mo...Help!

01:23:41.100 --> 01:23:42.393
Morris! Hey, hey,
come on, come on.

01:23:42.476 --> 01:23:44.103
Justin!
Doris!

01:23:44.186 --> 01:23:46.731
Call an ambulance!

01:23:46.814 --> 01:23:49.817
Oh, my God.
Don't leave me.

01:23:49.900 --> 01:23:52.695
Don't leave me.

01:23:52.778 --> 01:23:54.947
Don't leave me.

01:23:55.031 --> 01:23:56.198
Morris!

01:23:56.240 --> 01:23:58.200
Don't leave me!

01:23:58.284 --> 01:24:00.619
Help!
Help_

01:24:48.501 --> 01:24:50.002
I'm sorry,
I'm sorry.

01:24:50.086 --> 01:24:51.462
Everything's fine.
I'm sorry.

01:24:51.545 --> 01:24:52.922
Everything's fine.

01:24:52.963 --> 01:24:55.508
Everything's fine,
I'm sorry.

01:24:55.591 --> 01:24:57.927
<i>Everything's fine.
Rich'?</i>

01:24:57.968 --> 01:25:00.362
Sam!
Are you drunk?

01:25:00.546 --> 01:25:06.143
Shhh.
I don't want anyone to know.

01:25:06.227 --> 01:25:09.188
Everyone knows.

01:25:09.271 --> 01:25:10.314
Can I talk to you outside?

01:25:23.327 --> 01:25:24.411
Look, man...

01:25:27.790 --> 01:25:29.500
you got to understand.
People in my family

01:25:29.583 --> 01:25:31.085
don't come
to these things sober.

01:25:37.049 --> 01:25:40.719
Sam, I'm sorry.

01:25:40.803 --> 01:25:42.054
He was like
a father to me.

01:25:48.561 --> 01:25:49.895
<i>He wasn't your dad.</i>

01:25:57.945 --> 01:25:59.029
He was mine.

01:26:36.025 --> 01:26:38.194
You're not going
to hit me, are you?

01:26:40.571 --> 01:26:43.199
No.

01:26:43.282 --> 01:26:44.283
<i>Well...</i>

01:26:44.366 --> 01:26:46.619
probably not.

01:26:46.702 --> 01:26:49.914
But if I would,
you would deserve it.

01:26:49.997 --> 01:26:52.708
Yeah, I would.
I do.

01:26:55.878 --> 01:26:58.714
Now what?

01:26:58.797 --> 01:27:01.300
I was thinking
the same thing.

01:27:01.383 --> 01:27:06.889
You sticking
around Wichita?

01:27:06.931 --> 01:27:12.645
You know I left Nashville
to be with your dad.

01:27:12.728 --> 01:27:15.314
Okay, Richard.

01:27:15.397 --> 01:27:17.066
<i>So now what are
you going to do?</i>

01:27:19.401 --> 01:27:20.903
I don't know.

01:27:20.986 --> 01:27:22.446
What would you
tell somebody

01:27:22.529 --> 01:27:24.073
in your exact situation?

01:27:24.156 --> 01:27:25.908
And I know you know
the answer to this.

01:27:25.950 --> 01:27:27.534
If I was talking
to somebody else,

01:27:27.618 --> 01:27:29.203
I'd give them
the Sunday School answer.

01:27:29.286 --> 01:27:30.663
And what
is wrong with that?

01:27:30.746 --> 01:27:33.666
My dad was a...

01:27:33.749 --> 01:27:36.460
My dad was
a Sunday School teacher

01:27:36.543 --> 01:27:38.254
for 20 years.

01:27:38.337 --> 01:27:40.756
If there's one thing
that I learned from him,

01:27:40.839 --> 01:27:43.008
I learned that sometimes
the Sunday School answers

01:27:43.092 --> 01:27:45.844
are exactly
the right ones.

01:27:45.928 --> 01:27:46.971
<i>So what is it?</i>

01:27:50.266 --> 01:27:52.455
That God loves you even
when you don't feel it but...

01:27:52.456 --> 01:27:53.556
Exactly.

01:27:54.395 --> 01:27:55.771
Exactly.

01:27:55.854 --> 01:27:57.856
But the truth is
I don't get it.

01:27:57.940 --> 01:28:00.442
Even when I'm supposed to
know it, I just don't feel it.

01:28:00.484 --> 01:28:04.363
So, what do you know?
What do you feel?

01:28:06.031 --> 01:28:09.201
I feel broken.

01:28:09.285 --> 01:28:12.496
The only thing that
makes me feel... good

01:28:12.579 --> 01:28:14.999
is... not pretending otherwise.

01:28:15.082 --> 01:28:18.711
Well, I think
that's a good place to start.

01:28:22.965 --> 01:28:27.219
You know we're going
to be okay, right?

01:28:27.303 --> 01:28:28.804
We're going to be okay.

01:28:32.683 --> 01:28:34.560
I hope so.

01:29:01.670 --> 01:29:04.214
<i>Losing Morris
was devastating.</i>

01:29:04.298 --> 01:29:06.008
<i>And left me
at another crossroads</i>

01:29:06.091 --> 01:29:08.761
<i>in my life.</i>

01:29:08.844 --> 01:29:10.712
<i>I came to Wichita
to find myself,</i>

01:29:10.713 --> 01:29:15.768
<i>only to leave feeling
just as lost as I had before.</i>

01:29:15.851 --> 01:29:18.437
<i>I set out on the road
again with Justin,</i>

01:29:18.520 --> 01:29:19.897
<i>not really sure
where I was headed.</i>

01:29:27.988 --> 01:29:30.574
Hey, Rich.

01:29:30.657 --> 01:29:32.034
Where were you?

01:29:32.076 --> 01:29:33.700
I was just getting some food.

01:29:33.703 --> 01:29:37.581
Don't go anywhere without telling
me where you're going.  Okay?

01:29:37.664 --> 01:29:39.458
Okay.
Is everything all right?

01:29:39.541 --> 01:29:41.209
- I was just...
- I don't need you to talk.

01:29:41.210 --> 01:29:44.213
Just, if you're going somewhere,
tell me where you're going.

01:29:44.296 --> 01:29:46.799
Okay?
Or take me with you.

01:29:46.882 --> 01:29:48.717
- Okay, but...
- Damn it.

01:29:55.057 --> 01:29:57.935
Hey, can I play you a tape?

01:29:58.018 --> 01:29:59.561
What is it?

01:29:59.645 --> 01:30:01.897
There's this preacher Brennan Manning.

01:30:01.939 --> 01:30:04.942
You should know better than to
even ask me to listen to a preacher.

01:30:05.025 --> 01:30:06.777
Just give it ten minutes.

01:30:15.661 --> 01:30:18.080
<i>In the 33 years
since I was first ambushed</i>

01:30:18.122 --> 01:30:19.915
<i>by Jesus in a little chapel</i>

01:30:19.957 --> 01:30:22.835
<i>in the mountains
of western Pennsylvania,</i>

01:30:22.918 --> 01:30:27.464
<i>and the literally thousands of
hours of prayer and meditation,</i>

01:30:27.548 --> 01:30:31.510
<i>silence, solitude
in those years,</i>

01:30:31.593 --> 01:30:35.097
<i>I am now
utterly convinced</i>

01:30:35.139 --> 01:30:37.349
that on Judgment Day

01:30:37.433 --> 01:30:43.689
the Lord Jesus will ask one
question and only one question,

01:30:43.772 --> 01:30:45.732
"Did you believe
that I loved you?

01:30:48.193 --> 01:30:51.196
<i>"That I desired you?</i>

01:30:51.280 --> 01:30:56.034
<i>"That I waited
for you day after day?</i>

01:30:56.118 --> 01:31:00.956
"That I longed to hear
the sound of your voice?"

01:31:00.998 --> 01:31:03.959
The real believers
will respond and say,

01:31:04.001 --> 01:31:06.295
"I believed in your love,

01:31:06.378 --> 01:31:10.632
"and I tried to shape
my life as a response to it."

01:31:10.716 --> 01:31:14.094
<i>But many of us who are
so faithful in our ministry,</i>

01:31:14.178 --> 01:31:17.723
<i>our practice,
church going,</i>

01:31:17.806 --> 01:31:19.308
<i>are going to answer</i>

01:31:19.391 --> 01:31:22.519
"Well, frankly, no sir.

01:31:22.603 --> 01:31:25.856
"I never really believed it."

01:31:25.939 --> 01:31:29.234
And there's the difference
between the real believers

01:31:29.318 --> 01:31:32.988
<i>and the nominal Christians that
abound in our churches across the land.</i>

01:31:33.030 --> 01:31:36.033
<i>No one can measure
like a believer</i>

01:31:36.116 --> 01:31:39.244
<i>the depth and intensity
of God's love.</i>

01:31:39.328 --> 01:31:41.038
<i>But then again, no one
can measure like a believer</i>

01:31:41.121 --> 01:31:43.582
the effectiveness of
our gloom, our pessimism,

01:31:43.665 --> 01:31:47.252
our low self-esteem,
our self-hatred and despair

01:31:47.336 --> 01:31:50.339
that block God's way to us.

01:31:50.380 --> 01:31:52.216
<i>Do you see now
why it's so important</i>

01:31:52.299 --> 01:31:55.761
<i>to lay hold of this basic
truth of our faith?</i>

01:31:55.844 --> 01:32:00.766
<i>Because you're only going to be
as big as your own concept of God.</i>

01:32:00.849 --> 01:32:02.351
We make God in our own image

01:32:02.434 --> 01:32:05.354
and he winds up being
as fussy and rude

01:32:05.395 --> 01:32:08.023
and narrow-minded and
judgmental and legalistic

01:32:08.065 --> 01:32:11.401
and unloving
and unforgiving as we are.

01:32:11.485 --> 01:32:15.197
<i>I've been in churches in
Bangor, Maine, Miami, Seattle,</i>

01:32:15.280 --> 01:32:18.283
<i>San Diego, and Saint Louis,
and honest to God</i>

01:32:18.367 --> 01:32:22.746
if so many Christians
I meet is too small for me.

01:32:22.829 --> 01:32:24.915
Because he is
not the God of the Word.

01:32:24.998 --> 01:32:28.418
He is not the God who is revealed
in and by Jesus Christ,

01:32:28.502 --> 01:32:31.964
who at this moment comes
to your seat and says,

01:32:32.047 --> 01:32:35.050
I have a word for you.

01:32:35.092 --> 01:32:37.719
<i>I know your whole life story.</i>

01:32:37.803 --> 01:32:39.545
<i>I know every
skeleton in your closet.</i>

01:32:39.546 --> 01:32:42.966
<i>I know every moment of sin
and shame and dishonesty</i>

01:32:43.049 --> 01:32:45.811
<i>and degraded love
that's darkened your past.</i>

01:32:45.894 --> 01:32:49.940
<i>Right now, I know your shallow
faith, your feeble prayer life,</i>

01:32:50.023 --> 01:32:52.776
<i>your inconsistent discipleship,</i>

01:32:52.859 --> 01:32:56.321
<i>and my word
to you is this.</i>

01:32:56.405 --> 01:32:59.575
I dare you to trust
that I love you,

01:33:01.743 --> 01:33:03.912
just as you are.

01:33:03.954 --> 01:33:05.998
Not as you should be.

01:33:08.458 --> 01:33:11.461
Because none of us
are as we should be.

01:33:15.173 --> 01:33:18.510
<i>Whoa, what's up?
Are you all right?</i>

01:33:20.262 --> 01:33:23.640
<i>Rich.</i>

01:33:23.724 --> 01:33:24.766
Rich?

01:33:51.251 --> 01:33:53.462
You know, Brennan,
I've been going to church

01:33:53.545 --> 01:33:57.382
since I was less
than a week old.

01:33:57.466 --> 01:34:01.511
I can count on one hand how many times
I've heard the simple proclamation

01:34:01.595 --> 01:34:04.973
of what the Gospel
is really about.

01:34:05.015 --> 01:34:08.310
There are very few things
I love more than beer.

01:34:08.352 --> 01:34:11.355
Hot fudge sundae
is one of them.

01:34:11.438 --> 01:34:14.149
<i>Beer, huh'?
Mm-hm.</i>

01:34:14.191 --> 01:34:16.818
Yeah, I'm a recovering
alcoholic.

